summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 25490, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing and directing the City Engineer to incur an indebtedness in an amount not to exceed Twelve Hundred Dollars ($1200.00) against the General Fund on account of the cost and expense of the improvement of Fifteenth Avenue West and Thorndyk Avenue by planking, as authorized by Ordinance No. 24682, creating Local Improvement District No. 2374," passed over Mayor's veto October 31st, 1910.
